bib.title: Constraint on the astrophysical 18Ne(a,p)21Nareaction rate through a 24Mg(p,t)22Mg measurement

free_txt: Large area annular silicon detector array
SIDAR, configured with 100 mu-m dE detectors
backed by 1000-mu-m E detectors arranged in a
"lampshade" configuration to cover a large angular
range.The angles covered by SIDAR were between 18deg
and 48deg for E=41MeV and between 27deg and 69deg
